pageContext.claim: “They set up these caravans. In many cases, they put their worst people in the caravan; they're not going to put their best in. They get rid of their problems.”
pageContext.analysis: There's no evidence that Honduras, Guatemala or El Salvador organized any of the caravans walking north or that they are sending "their worst people." While there are bound to be a few bad apples in any large group, many of the people travelling north are families.
